# SQL Query Explanations

## Query 1 – Return all employees and their departments

Retrieves all employees along with their employee ID, email address, and department from the **employees** table.

---

## Query 2 – Return employees who have completed all assigned trainings

Returns employees for whom every assigned training has a status of **Completed**. Employees with any incomplete training are excluded.

---

## Query 3 – Count trainings per employee

Counts the total number of training records assigned to each employee. A **LEFT JOIN** is used to include employees who have not yet been assigned any training.

---

## Query 4 – Certifications expiring within 30 days

Returns certifications whose expiry date falls within the next 30 days. This helps identify certifications that require renewal.

---

## Query 5 – Employees with overdue trainings

Returns employees who still have one or more trainings that have not been completed.

---

## Query 6 – Top 5 employees by completed trainings

Returns the five employees with the highest number of completed trainings, ordered from highest to lowest.
